Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2015 17:45:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 34/65] gpio: gpiolib: initialize the local variable 'gpio' to
 ARCH_NR_GPIOS in function 'gpiod_set_drive' due to
 klocwork warning.

Signed-off-by: Ang, Chee Hong <chee.hong.ang@intel.com>
Change-Id: I0acb0f107311b3fcfc49ef04491552fb838c4f90
Reviewed-on: https://git-gar-1.devtools.intel.com/gerrit/5314
Reviewed-by: Fung, Joshua <joshua.fung@intel.com>
Tested-by: Tan, Raymond <raymond.tan@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Pengyu Ma <pengyu.ma@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/gpio/gpiolib.c |    3 ++-
 1 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpio/gpiolib.c b/drivers/gpio/gpiolib.c
index e60720a..7140a7f 100644
--- a/drivers/gpio/gpiolib.c
+++ b/drivers/gpio/gpiolib.c
@@ -1119,7 +1119,8 @@ int gpiod_set_drive(struct gpio_desc *desc, unsigned mode)
 	unsigned long		flags;
 	struct gpio_chip	*chip;
 	int			status = -EINVAL;
-	unsigned gpio = ~0;
+	unsigned gpio = ARCH_NR_GPIOS;
+
 	spin_lock_irqsave(&gpio_lock, flags);
 
 	if (!desc || !desc->chip) {
